title: unicode/utf8 link is broken.
body:
http://golang.org/pkg/unicode/utf8/ shows this error: `/src/unicode/utf8/utf8.go:385:6: expected operand, found 'range' (and 3 more errors)`. http://golang.org/pkg/unicode/ works but not http://golang.org/pkg/unicode/utf8

What version of Go are you using (go version)? `go 1.4`

What operating system and processor architecture are you using? `Ubuntu 14.10`

What did you do? Click http://golang.org/pkg/unicode/utf8/

What did you expect to see? `utf8` package documentation.

What did you see instead? `/src/unicode/utf8/utf8.go:385:6: expected operand, found 'range' (and 3 more errors)`

Thank you!
